# Octopus workflow commands (RM-113). One command per line, pipe-delimited.
# Fields: name|description
#
# This file is the single source of truth for the workflow CLI:
#   - cli/octopus.sh generates its help from it and rejects any name not
#     listed here, so helper/implementation libs in cli/lib/ (ui, audit-map,
#     knowledge-*, consigliere-lens, setup-picker) are never dispatched as
#     commands.
#   - bin/octopus reads it to list the workflow commands in `octopus help`.
# Adding a command = a new cli/lib/<name>.sh plus one line here.
#
# The global bootstrap commands (install, update, doctor) live in the
# bin/octopus shim, not here.
setup|Configure Octopus in the current repository (--reconfigure to edit)
uninstall|Remove Octopus artifacts from the current repository
branch-create|Create a development branch
dev-flow|Run the guided development workflow
pr-open|Open a PR following conventions
pr-review|Self-review a PR and assign reviewers
pr-comments|Address PR review comments
pr-merge|Merge an approved PR
release|Create a versioned release with tag and CHANGELOG
control|Open the TUI agent dashboard
ask|Dispatch a task to a specific agent with live streaming output
run|Run a feature end-to-end: requirement to spec to plan to agents to PR
kr|Query the knowledge-root registry (list/meta/nodes/links/archive)
hygiene|Audit a knowledge root (staleness/orphans/links/archive)
synthesize|Surface cross-node connections in a knowledge root
briefing|Proactive cadence summary over a knowledge root
lens|Surface consigliere lens-context (playbook + political risk)
